    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-28T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/7–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-28T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 28, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 28—12:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>395. My 393, July 28.<note n="15" xml:id="d262fn1">Not printed.</note> Ganev has
                    just suggested to me that a statement by Voice of America in Bulgarian of
                    substance of Petkov’s letter<note n="16" xml:id="d262fn2">See telegrams 385,
                        July 27, 10 a.m., and 286, July 27, from Sofia, <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_722">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Potsdam</hi>), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 722</ref> and
                            <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_724">724</ref>, respectively.</note>
                    requesting application to Bulgaria of Yalta Declaration and tripartite Allied
                    control over Bulgarian elections when they are held and indicating approval in
                    US of this expression of desire for democratic procedures in Bulgaria might have
                    a most beneficial effect at this time on Bulgarian political situation. If Dept
                    and OWI approves word to this effect would be greatly appreciated by me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
